FT  07 JUL 93 / Observer: Which princess?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ever wondered how far you can go on a River Thames pleasure boat from
Westminster pier? Greenwich, Richmond and Hampton Court are regular ports of
call. But the shipping casualty report in yesterday's Lloyd's List notes
that the Royal Princess was on a cruise from Amsterdam when it bumped in to
Southwark Bridge on Sunday.
Had the skipper been on the helm too long?
</TEXT>
