FT  07 JUL 93 / British justice: weighing up the alternatives
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GUARDING AGAINST MISCARRIAGES OF JUSTICE
An independent review authority to investigate alleged miscarriages of
justice
Continuous video recording of police custody suites and of police
interrogations
Allowing judges in exceptional cases to order selection of a jury containing
up to three people from ethnic minority communities
THE DRIVE FOR EFFICIENCY
Abolition of the defendant's right to elect jury trial
Inroads into defendants' right to silence by requiring disclosure of defence
case before trial
Introduction of a formal system of sentence discounts for early guilty
pleas.
