<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 93 / Airports to reduce night flights
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NEW night-flying restrictions designed to cut noise at Heathrow, Gatwick and
Stansted airports are to start in October, David Owen writes.
The government announced yesterday that a new quota system based on the
noise of different types of aircraft would be introduced, replacing the
current regime based on the number of aircraft movements.
Under the new system, the louder the aircraft, the more its use at night
will use up an airport's quota.
Separate regulations will ensure that louder aircraft, such as the BAC 1-11,
will be phased out within a decade. The new system is to operate for five
years.
