<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 93 / World Trade News: Machine tool deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
JONES &amp; SHIPMAN, the UK machine tool builder, has won an important Pounds
400,000 order from Tong Nam Precision, a South Korean toolmaker, for one of
its sophisticated 'creep-feed' grinding machines.
J&amp;S described the order as a breakthrough in terms of industrial application
and market.
Creep-feed grinding involves passing the component under the grinding wheel
at a slow pace, allowing more metal to be removed. The order for Tong Nam
includes a cylindrical grinding machine.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Jones and Shipman.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>KRZ  South Korea, Asia.
</CN>
