FT  06 JUL 93 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GOLD closed lower on the London bullion market after initial support from
European investor buying was capped by producer selling. Dealers still saw
the recent rally carrying the yellow metal through the psychologically
significant Dollars 400 a troy ounce. But technical analysts expect
significant resistance at that level. COPPER prices closed higher on the
LME, while other metals closed mixed after a largely lacklustre day. Dealers
said there was little market-moving news and, with the US market closed for
Independence Day, the LME lacked interest for long periods.
Compiled from Reuters
