<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 93 / International Company News: BankAmerica Corp
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BANKAMERICA Corp's Bank of America subsidiary is forming an organisation,
based on wholesale and retail banking divisions, to serve its Asia markets
more effectively, Reuter reports from San Francisco.
The organisation will include an Asian wholesale banking division and an
Asian retail banking division, both based in Hong Kong.
Mr James Hulihan, chief executive officer of Bank of America (Asia), will
head the retail division, and Mr Kai Nargolwala, senior credit officer with
the Asia division, will lead the wholesale division.
